bmo: Thanks for the quick check-in — I see why you’re not seeing BMO_SOURCE show up.

Root cause
- The default BMO_SOURCE logic lives in tools/lib.mjs, but index.mjs only printed the raw environment variable and didn’t surface the effective value resolved by the tools lib.
- So even though tools wrote with mirroring if BMO_SOURCE was resolved, the startup banner didn’t reflect it, and the process env didn’t get the inferred value.

Fixes applied
- Default path updated previously to ~/src/bmo-agent (kept).
- index.mjs now:
  - Imports tools/lib.mjs on startup.
  - If env BMO_SOURCE is not set but lib.BMO_SOURCE is, sets process.env.BMO_SOURCE to lib.BMO_SOURCE.
  - Prints Effective BMO_SOURCE: ... so you can see what’s actually being used by tools.

What to do
- Rebuild/reinstall bmo.
- Run it from another directory and check the banner:
  - You should see Effective BMO_SOURCE: /Users/…/src/bmo-agent if that directory exists.
- Writes to bmo://tools/... will mirror to ~/src/bmo-agent/tools.

